We've just updated our InfoREXX multimedia help file for OS/2, Windows,
and Windows NT to include the new language syntax for Object REXX (as
distributed in the Object REXX beta on volume 6 of The Developer
Connection for OS/2 released in early Feb 1995).  First of all, let me
say that the .INF documentation distributed with the beta is abysmal
(yes, I'm not an impartial judge here).  There are many omissions and
inconsistencies.

By the way, the March issue of our INTER REXX newsletter will carry a
6-page in-depth feature article on Object REXX.

Below is the main topic page in InfoREXX for the Object REXX language
extensions.  Note that this is NOT at all the way in which the Object
REXX .INF file is organized.

